### **Electrodynamics (Current Electricity, EMI, AC) (12 Questions)**

19. **Kirchhoff's second law is based on the law of conservation of:**
    A. Charge
    B. Energy
    C. Mass
    D. Momentum
    **Answer: B**

20. **The resistance of a wire is R. If it is stretched to double its length, the new resistance will be:**
    A. R
    B. 2R
    C. 4R
    D. R/4
    **Answer: C**

21. **A galvanometer can be converted into an ammeter by connecting:**
    A. A low resistance in parallel
    B. A high resistance in parallel
    C. A low resistance in series
    D. A high resistance in series
    **Answer: A**

22. **The SI unit of electric potential is:**
    A. Coulomb
    B. Joule
    C. Volt
    D. Ampere
    **Answer: C**

23. **A charged particle enters a uniform magnetic field perpendicular to its direction. Its path in the field will be:**
    A. Straight line
    B. Circle
    C. Ellipse
    D. Parabola
    **Answer: B**

24. **The self-inductance of a solenoid depends on:**
    A. Only the current
    B. Only the number of turns
    C. Only the length
    D. Geometry and permeability of core
    **Answer: D**

25. **The power factor of a purely resistive AC circuit is:**
    A. 0
    B. 0.5
    C. 1
    D. Infinite
    **Answer: C**

26. **In a transformer, the number of turns in the primary coil is 100 and that in the secondary coil is 1000. If the input voltage is 200 V, the output voltage is:**
    A. 20 V
    B. 2000 V
    C. 200 V
    D. 20,000 V
    **Answer: B**

27. **Lenz's law is a consequence of the law of conservation of:**
    A. Charge
    B. Mass
    C. Energy
    D. Momentum
    **Answer: C**

28. **Two bulbs of 100 W and 200 W rated at 220 V are connected in series to a 220 V supply. The power consumed will be:**
    A. 33.3 W
    B. 66.6 W
    C. 100 W
    D. 150 W
    **Answer: B**

29. **The direction of the magnetic field around a straight current-carrying conductor is given by:**
    A. Fleming's left-hand rule
    B. Fleming's right-hand rule
    C. Right-hand thumb rule
    D. Ampere's swimming rule
    **Answer: C**

30. **The principle of an electric generator is based on:**
    A. Heating effect of current
    B. Chemical effect of current
    C. Electromagnetic induction
    D. Magnetic effect of current
    **Answer: C**

